{
  "id": "019cfb6c-c71f-7a10-86d6-1cc9ac7f528a",
  "content": "## 05_resolve_setup.py — Implementation Complete\n\nPhase 5 DaVinci Resolve setup script implemented at `scripts/05_resolve_setup.py`. Key design decisions:\n\n### Architecture\n- Single-file implementation following existing pipeline script patterns (workspace root resolution, config loading, logging format)\n- Runs on the HOST machine only (not in devcontainer) — requires running DaVinci Resolve Studio and fusionscript.so\n- Each Resolve API interaction wrapped in its own function with try/except error handling\n- Defensive coding throughout: every API call returns None/False on failure, caller continues gracefully\n\n### Resolve API Workflow\n1. Connect to running Resolve via `DaVinciResolveScript.scriptapp(\"Resolve\")`\n2. Get or create project (checks current project first, then tries LoadProject, then CreateProject)\n3. Create Media Pool subfolder structure: `Footage/{date}/`\n4. Import all footage clips from `footage/raw/{date}/` and `footage/flat/{date}/`\n5. Create timeline named `Dive_{date}` from imported clips\n6. For each timeline item:\n   a. Apply DRX template (deploys 8-node grade structure)\n   b. Set LUT on Node 1 (Base LUT)\n   c. Find and attach depth sequence as external matte on Node 3\n   d. Load scene analysis, assign subjects to nodes, attach mask mattes\n\n### 8-Node Structure (Section 5.1)\nNode constants defined as module-level integers (1-based indexing):\n- Node 1: Base LUT — receives .cube LUT via SetLUT()\n- Node 2: Neutral Balance — no automated setup\n- Node 3: Depth Grade — receives depth map sequence as external matte\n- Node 4: Foreground Pop — receives primary subject mask\n- Node 5: Diver — receives diver mask\n- Node 6: Marine Life — receives marine life mask\n- Node 7: Creative Look — no automated setup\n- Node 8: Output — no automated setup\n\n### Subject-to-Node Mapping\n- Labels containing \"diver\" -> Node 5\n- Labels matching marine life keywords (extensive set: wrasse, fish, turtle, ray, shark, etc.) -> Node 6\n- All other subjects -> Node 4 (foreground)\n- Each node gets at most one subject (first match wins); extras logged as unassigned\n- Marine life keywords include species names, coral types, and marine invertebrates\n\n### External Matte Attachment\n- Primary method: `SetNodeExternalMatte(node_index, matte_path)` \n- Fallback method: `SetClipProperty(\"ExternalMatte\", matte_path)`\n- If both fail, logs warning suggesting manual attachment in Color page\n- The Resolve scripting API for per-node external mattes varies across versions, so both approaches are attempted\n\n### Error Handling\n- DaVinciResolveScript import failure: clear error about environment setup and host requirement\n- Resolve not running: clear error about starting Resolve first\n- DRX template not found: warn and skip (LUT still applied)\n- LUT file not found: warn and continue\n- Missing mask/depth sequences: log warning, continue with remaining clips\n- Any Resolve API call failure: log error, continue with remaining clips\n\n### Config Keys Used\n- `footage_raw`, `footage_flat` (footage directories)\n- `working_dir` (for masks, depth, scene_analysis paths)\n- `resolve_lut_path` (default: repos/dorea/luts/underwater_base.cube)\n- `resolve_drx_path` (default: repos/dorea/templates/underwater_grade_v1.drx)\n- `resolve_project_name` (default: Dive_2026)\n\n### CLI\n- `--date YYYY-MM-DD` (required)\n- `--verbose` / `-v` — debug logging\n\n### Testing Limitations\n- Cannot test against live Resolve instance from devcontainer\n- Verified: py_compile passes, --help works, unit tests pass for classify_subject, assign_subjects_to_nodes, find_workspace_root\n- Resolve API calls are structured defensively but untested against real API",
